				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well topic says it all really. What I'm working on at the moment is a flatroll which creates a number based on random seed that I can add weight to for various people based on various factors.
<br />

<br />
What i'm looking at doing is (for example) adding 2 points into the mysql table for previous raids attended by a person. Then a points bonus based on level (215 = +0 ; 216 = +1 etc..).
<br />

<br />
So what i'd end up with is...
<br />

<br />
persons A, B, C add to a roll for an item
<br />
Calculate: random number (900-950?) for each person. Then add weight.
<br />

<br />
So it could possibly look like...
<br />

<br />
A: 950 (+2 (his first raid) +1 (he is 216) ) = 953
<br />
b: 944 (+10 (five raids in) +5 (he is 220) ) = 959
<br />
c: 931 (+4 (second raid) +3 (he is 218) ) = 938
<br />

<br />
Even though B rolled lower than A, he won because of previous attendance. His raidpoints are now reset, but his level bonus will obviously remain.
<br />

<br />
Question is.. what is a good way to arrive at the first number? Anyone got any genius ideas on a reasonable and fair way to do this? 
<br />

<br />
Thanks in anticipation <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
