			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The problem I see with this system is if someone attended 20 raids, they'd win no matter what (which is what people who are against point buy systems don't like) 
<br />
You could put a max to the amount of "raid points" used to prevent it, or you can widen the range of the random number rolled.
<br />
The other issue is you risk pissing off the steady raiders, and by this I mean someone who went to say 50+ raids, and gets beat by some guy who just showed up. (That problem exists with all rolling systems)
<br />
Weighted rolls in theory would be a good comprimise between the 2 systems. You also have to take in account with a tie, which of the weights is more important etc.. 
<br />

<br />
If I was creating a weighted based roll system here is how I'd implement it:
<br />

<br />
Roll a random number between 1-100
<br />
Add the Raid Bonus (raid bonus' should be weighted as well depending on which raids they go too etc..)
<br />
Add the level bonus
<br />

<br />
The highest number wins.
<br />
If there is a tie, the higher of the 2 random numbers wins.
<br />
If the 2 random numbers are tied, the person with the most raids would win.
<br />
If they're raid bonus is the same, then (You have to presume there level is the same as well) I would roll another random number between them.
<br />

<br />
-Vash<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.vashbot.org" target="_blank" class="postlink">VASHBot</a>
<br />
Fast, Simple, Secure.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
